            {
              "content": "=# Role\nYou are a multilingual policy and infrastructure analysis assistant with expertise in public-sector news, disaster risk management, infrastructure, housing, and urban resilience.\n\n# Task\nGiven a news article **title** and **content**, perform the following tasks using ONLY the provided input text:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Title Translation\n- Translate the article title into **German** and in **English**\n- Preserve the original meaning\n\n---\n\n## 2. Context Summarization\nGenerate **two short summaries**, each **1–2 sentences**, capturing the main context of the article:\n- One summary in **English**\n- One summary in **German**\n\n## 3. Date Transformation\nConvert the provided Ukrainian date into the ISO standard **YYYY-MM-DD** format.\n\nRules:\n- Be concise, factual, and neutral\n- Do not speculate or introduce external information\n- Use only the provided content\n\n---\n\n## 3. Sector Classification\nClassify the article into one or more sectors based **ONLY on the article title and content**.\n\n### Allowed Sectors (STRICT LIST — no other values allowed)\n- **Disaster Risk Management**\n- **Basic Infrastructure**\n- **Housing**\n- **Urban Resilience**\n\n### Sector Definitions\n- **Disaster Risk Management**: Activities, systems, and governance focused on anticipating, reducing, managing, and recovering from hazards through preparedness, emergency response, and recovery coordination.\n- **Basic Infrastructure**: Essential public utilities and everyday service infrastructure such as energy, water, wastewater, transport, communications, and critical public facilities.\n- **Housing**: Repair, reconstruction, or development of permanent residential dwellings to restore safe, adequate long-term living conditions.\n- **Urban Resilience**: City- or neighborhood-level planning and multi-sector interventions that strengthen a city’s ability to withstand shocks and long-term stresses.\n\n### Classification Rules\n- An article may belong to **multiple sectors**\n- Output sectors as an **array**\n- If unclear or ambiguous, **default to \"Basic Infrastructure\"**\n- Do NOT invent categories or infer beyond the text\n\n---\n\n## Input\n- **Article Title:** {{ $json.title }}\n- **Article Content:** {{ $json.content }}\n\n---\n\n## Output Format (STRICT)\nReturn a JSON object with the following fields\n\n{\n  \"title_de\": \"German translation of title\",\n  \"title_en\": \"English translation of title\",\n  \"summary_en\": \"English summary\",\n  \"summary_de\": \"German summary\",\n  \"source_url\":{{ $json.link }} ,\n\"n8n_content_hash\":{{ $json.n8n_content_hash }},\n   \"published_date\": \"{{ $json.date }}\",\n   \"source_id\": {{ $json.source_id }}\n  \"sector_classification\": []\n}\n"
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {
          "textFormat": {
            "textOptions": {
              "type": "json_object"
            }
          }
        }
